document_data.History:
In The Year of Despair, Malatran calendar, late 14{{th}} century [[DR]], a group of heroes of the Living Jungle were sent from the [[Malatran Plateau]] through an elemental ''[[portal|gate]]'' to the far-away world of Athas. Immediately upon arrival, the group was captured by [[Athasian elf]] slavers. A young [[thri-kreen]] named [[Ka'cha]] was among creatures captured by the elves, and he lamented being separated from his clutch.<ref>{{Cite organized play/LJ/Dark Suns|9}} Subsequently, the heroes escaped when the elven caravan was attacked by a hungry [[sink worm]]. They seized the opportunity and freed Ka'cha, fleeing from their pursuers across the desert.<ref>{{Cite organized play/LJ/Dark Suns|13}}

After two days of travel across the hot sands, guided by Ka'cha, the group stumbled across his tribe, the [[Windrunners]], and their leader, [[Ki'rik'ku]]. Ka'cha convinced them that the strange adventurers were friends, not food. Happy with one of their number returned, Chief Ki'rik'ku gifted the aliens four large [[erdlu]] [[egg]]s and two ''[[potion fruit|apples of healing]]''. The thri-kreen then explained to the Malatran heroes how to reach their destination&ndash;the [[Ringing Forest]]&ndash;the way back to [[Toril]].{{Cite organized play/LJ/Dark Suns|14}}

While traveling to the forest through a path in the [[Ringing Mountains]], the Malatran heroes found themselves under attack by a particularly hungry cloud ray.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Dark Suns|20-21}}
